# AgriOps MCP server

Reference implementation of an MCP server that exposes Japanese agricultural data — farmland polygons (eMAFF), 1 km weather (Open-Meteo / JMA), and pesticide registrations (FAMIC) — to AI agents.

## What it does

- `search_farmland` — eMAFF Fude polygon search by address / prefecture / crop.
- `get_weather_1km` — hourly weather forecast at lat/lng (Open-Meteo, CC-BY 4.0).
- `area_summary` / `nearby_farms` / `get_pesticide_rules` — derived queries.
- Phase 2: 5 user-controlled prompts (slash commands).
- Phase 3: Form-mode elicitation when input is missing.
- Phase 4: URL-mode elicitation + OAuth Client Credentials.
- Phase 5: MCP Apps UI dashboard (`ui://agriops/dashboard.html`).

